1
00:00:01,390 --> 00:00:03,617
<i>Three weeks ago,
an invisible dome crashed down</i>

2
00:00:03,653 --> 00:00:08,283
<i>on Chester's Mill, cutting us
off from the rest of the world.</i>

3
00:00:08,668 --> 00:00:11,269
<i>The dome has tested
our limits...</i>

4
00:00:11,271 --> 00:00:12,504
Go!

5
00:00:12,506 --> 00:00:14,306
<i>...pitting us against
one another.</i>

6
00:00:14,308 --> 00:00:17,576
Chester's Mill sentences
Dale Barbara to death.

7
00:00:17,578 --> 00:00:18,437
<i>...and forcing each of us</i>

8
00:00:18,473 --> 00:00:20,445
<i>to confront our own
personal demons...</i>

9
00:00:20,481 --> 00:00:22,914
<i>rage...</i>

10
00:00:22,916 --> 00:00:25,784
I need to know that you will
stand with me against <i>that!</i>

11
00:00:25,786 --> 00:00:26,874
<i>...grief...</i>

12
00:00:26,910 --> 00:00:28,687
I don't understand...
who could do this to her?

13
00:00:28,689 --> 00:00:31,923
I promise you, we're going
to catch whoever did this.

14
00:00:31,925 --> 00:00:33,758
- <i>...fear...</i>
- We're trapped.

15
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,127
<i>I hear we're going
to run out of water.</i>

16
00:00:39,867 --> 00:00:41,433
You killed Angie McAlister.

17
00:00:41,435 --> 00:00:43,502
<i>...shame.</i>

18
00:00:43,504 --> 00:00:45,467
I thought it would bring
the dome down.

19
00:00:45,503 --> 00:00:47,716
I would do anything
to take it back.

20
00:00:47,752 --> 00:00:50,909
<i>But we've also found love
under the dome.</i>

21
00:00:52,145 --> 00:00:56,314
<i>And we have battled to
keep our town together.</i>

22
00:00:57,416 --> 00:00:59,384
I thought the dome
was supposed to protect us.

23
00:00:59,386 --> 00:01:01,753
No, it's up to us
to protect each other.

24
00:01:01,755 --> 00:01:04,389
<i>Now we may finally have found
a way out.</i>

25
00:01:04,391 --> 00:01:06,992
We're outside the dome.

26
00:01:06,994 --> 00:01:08,560
<i>We hope it takes us home,</i>

27
00:01:08,562 --> 00:01:11,596
<i>but what if it takes us
to an alternate reality?</i>

28
00:01:11,598 --> 00:01:13,198
<i>Whatever's going down
in Chester's Mill,</i>

29
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:16,167
<i>here's proof
that it ain't real.</i>

30
00:01:16,169 --> 00:01:17,802
<i>These places...</i>

31
00:01:17,804 --> 00:01:19,146
<i>these people...</i>

32
00:01:19,182 --> 00:01:21,000
something is wrong here.

33
00:01:24,744 --> 00:01:25,911
What do you say, Red?

34
00:01:25,913 --> 00:01:27,090
Do it.

35
00:01:44,297 --> 00:01:45,363
You okay?

36
00:01:45,365 --> 00:01:47,365
Okay, stay close.

37
00:01:47,367 --> 00:01:48,333
Watch your step.

38
00:01:48,335 --> 00:01:50,335
Here, use your legs.
I got you.

39
00:01:50,337 --> 00:01:53,405
Come here, don't put
too much weight on it.

40
00:02:02,916 --> 00:02:04,215
Is this a joke?

41
00:02:13,092 --> 00:02:15,193
So what are we gonna do now?

42
00:02:15,195 --> 00:02:17,395
I'm getting so tired of this...

43
00:02:19,399 --> 00:02:21,866
It's all right.
It's gonna be all right.

44
00:02:21,868 --> 00:02:24,369
I just can't take this anymore.

45
00:02:31,079 --> 00:02:34,079
3x03 - <i>Redux</i>

46
00:02:36,849 --> 00:02:40,919
We walked
into the white light...

47
00:02:40,921 --> 00:02:43,588
and we just kept going.

48
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:45,924
And the dome was gone.

49
00:02:46,792 --> 00:02:49,828
And we were free.

50
00:02:49,830 --> 00:02:54,132
The outside world,
somehow it seemed more...

51
00:02:54,134 --> 00:02:56,668
more beautiful,

52
00:02:56,670 --> 00:02:59,804
you know, more vibrant.

53
00:02:59,806 --> 00:03:02,941
Where was I?

54
00:03:02,943 --> 00:03:05,176
You were dead.

55
00:03:09,448 --> 00:03:12,117
What did you do after I died?

56
00:03:12,119 --> 00:03:14,586
Julia...

57
00:03:14,588 --> 00:03:17,822
I want to know
what it was like for you.

58
00:03:17,824 --> 00:03:19,457
There was a funeral,

59
00:03:19,459 --> 00:03:22,861
and I met your parents.
The only thing I could do

60
00:03:22,863 --> 00:03:25,897
was to get as far away
from Chester's Mill as possible.

61
00:03:25,899 --> 00:03:27,432
Where'd you go?

62
00:03:28,267 --> 00:03:30,468
Abuja.

63
00:03:33,139 --> 00:03:34,472
Kabul.

64
00:03:34,474 --> 00:03:36,374
I ran rescue missions.

65
00:03:36,376 --> 00:03:38,743
I dreamt about you

66
00:03:38,745 --> 00:03:41,713
every night.

67
00:03:41,715 --> 00:03:44,516
Hey, it's okay.

68
00:03:44,518 --> 00:03:46,551
I met a woman.

69
00:03:51,323 --> 00:03:53,491
She doesn't matter.

70
00:03:53,493 --> 00:03:56,294
None of it was real.

71
00:03:59,131 --> 00:04:00,965
What happened to your neck?

72
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:03,401
Your father came back.

73
00:04:03,403 --> 00:04:04,736
He brought the egg.

74
00:04:04,738 --> 00:04:06,905
- My father did that?
- No.

75
00:04:08,842 --> 00:04:11,176
Don's dead.

76
00:04:12,011 --> 00:04:14,412
How?

77
00:04:14,414 --> 00:04:16,815
I think Melanie killed him.

78
00:04:16,817 --> 00:04:18,817
How could you even say that?

79
00:04:18,819 --> 00:04:22,320
Because she tried
to kill me, too.

80
00:04:41,540 --> 00:04:44,275
Found this in an emergency kit.

81
00:04:44,277 --> 00:04:46,444
You should eat something.

82
00:04:52,518 --> 00:04:54,753
Come on home.

83
00:04:54,755 --> 00:04:56,221
That's your home, not mine.

84
00:04:56,223 --> 00:04:59,090
Course it's yours.

85
00:04:59,092 --> 00:05:01,059
I-I don't know
how I'm back here.

86
00:05:01,994 --> 00:05:04,829
You were in some kind
of a-a, a-a cocoon,

87
00:05:04,831 --> 00:05:08,266
- and-and... you never went anywhere.
- I did.

88
00:05:08,268 --> 00:05:10,635
I moved on. I got rid of you.

89
00:05:11,437 --> 00:05:13,872
This time has to
be different, Dad.

90
00:05:15,941 --> 00:05:17,876
I want to forgive you.

91
00:05:17,878 --> 00:05:19,911
- For what?
- All of it.

92
00:05:19,913 --> 00:05:23,014
Locking me up
in that bomb shelter,

93
00:05:23,016 --> 00:05:26,184
alone, in the dark.

94
00:05:26,186 --> 00:05:28,887
Leaving me up in that tree,
forcing me

95
00:05:28,889 --> 00:05:30,655
to go get the belt.

96
00:05:32,158 --> 00:05:33,625
I saved you.

97
00:05:33,627 --> 00:05:34,926
You should be

98
00:05:34,928 --> 00:05:36,261
thanking me.

99
00:05:36,263 --> 00:05:37,695
You were a weak little kid.

100
00:05:37,697 --> 00:05:39,097
I just tried to make you strong.

101
00:05:39,099 --> 00:05:40,799
I was stronger without you.

102
00:05:40,801 --> 00:05:41,866
Where?!

103
00:05:41,868 --> 00:05:44,169
In your little make-believe
cocoon world?

104
00:05:44,171 --> 00:05:45,503
You're still weak.

105
00:05:45,505 --> 00:05:48,106
You're pathetic and afraid.

106
00:05:52,378 --> 00:05:55,647
You can punch that dome
as many times as you need to,

107
00:05:55,649 --> 00:05:57,248
Junior.

108
00:05:59,218 --> 00:06:02,187
You're back under it.

109
00:06:08,027 --> 00:06:10,762
Three weeks.

110
00:06:10,764 --> 00:06:13,464
That's how long you and I
were in those cocoons.

111
00:06:13,466 --> 00:06:15,500
My God.

112
00:06:15,502 --> 00:06:16,868
I know.

113
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:19,437
Christine...

114
00:06:19,439 --> 00:06:22,340
the last thing I remember
was us finding that egg.

115
00:06:22,342 --> 00:06:26,044
And then I was in an alternate
reality for, like, a year.

116
00:06:26,046 --> 00:06:29,480
In love with Dale,
carrying his child.

117
00:06:29,482 --> 00:06:31,049
And now we've hatched

118
00:06:31,051 --> 00:06:32,684
and we're under a dome?

119
00:06:32,686 --> 00:06:34,419
None of this makes sense.

120
00:06:34,421 --> 00:06:37,622
We're anthropologists.

121
00:06:37,624 --> 00:06:40,024
But in that world,
I was an aid worker.

122
00:06:40,026 --> 00:06:41,693
You-you were a therapist.

123
00:06:41,695 --> 00:06:43,428
Why were we different?

124
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:44,729
I can't tell you that,

125
00:06:44,731 --> 00:06:47,365
but...
I think it's a good thing.

126
00:06:47,367 --> 00:06:49,033
If this town knew

127
00:06:49,035 --> 00:06:52,103
who we really are, that
we were here to find that egg,

128
00:06:52,105 --> 00:06:54,439
we'd have a lot
more to answer for.

129
00:06:54,441 --> 00:06:56,174
All those hunts
Hektor sent us on,

130
00:06:56,176 --> 00:06:59,377
do you think Aktaion knew what
would happen when we found one?

131
00:06:59,379 --> 00:07:01,179
Tomorrow we'll go to
that town hall meeting

132
00:07:01,181 --> 00:07:03,882
- and find out what we can.
- No, I'm...

133
00:07:03,884 --> 00:07:06,484
I can't see Dale.
With her.

134
00:07:09,388 --> 00:07:11,389
We have to go.

135
00:07:11,391 --> 00:07:12,991
People saw us in those caves.

136
00:07:12,993 --> 00:07:15,560
If we don't show up,
they'll come looking.

137
00:07:15,562 --> 00:07:19,030
Is it possible I'm pregnant?

138
00:07:20,766 --> 00:07:24,202
I don't think so, hon.

139
00:07:24,204 --> 00:07:25,904
It felt so real.

140
00:07:25,906 --> 00:07:27,872
It still does.

141
00:07:27,874 --> 00:07:31,809
You have always talked
about wanting kids.

142
00:07:31,811 --> 00:07:33,845
It'll happen.

143
00:07:47,359 --> 00:07:50,862
I guess the best way of
explaining it is that we were in

144
00:07:50,864 --> 00:07:52,196
a simulated reality.

145
00:07:52,198 --> 00:07:54,232
Like <i>The Matrix.</i>

146
00:07:54,234 --> 00:07:55,900
Want to hear something weird?

147
00:07:55,902 --> 00:07:57,068
More weird

148
00:07:57,070 --> 00:07:58,703
than we were in a Matrix?

149
00:07:58,705 --> 00:08:00,171
I don't need my glasses anymore.

150
00:08:00,173 --> 00:08:01,439
I can see without them.

151
00:08:01,441 --> 00:08:04,809
Maybe the goo that was
all over us fixed your eyes.

152
00:08:04,811 --> 00:08:06,511
Well, yay, you can see,

153
00:08:06,513 --> 00:08:09,047
but we're still trapped
inside this hell bubble.

154
00:08:09,049 --> 00:08:10,315
Want my sweater?

155
00:08:11,850 --> 00:08:14,052
Yeah.

156
00:08:14,853 --> 00:08:17,455
Wh-What are you even doing here?

157
00:08:17,457 --> 00:08:20,625
I don't have a house to go to.

158
00:08:20,627 --> 00:08:22,493
Can we please go to sleep?

159
00:08:31,937 --> 00:08:35,106
Yesterday we were together.

160
00:08:35,108 --> 00:08:39,644
But in the Matrix,
you moved on without me.

161
00:08:41,413 --> 00:08:43,448
So...

162
00:08:43,450 --> 00:08:46,684
what are we now?

163
00:08:46,686 --> 00:08:50,321
I don't know.

164
00:08:50,323 --> 00:08:53,524
It feels like a year's passed.

165
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:57,428
And I feel...

166
00:08:57,430 --> 00:09:00,298
different.

167
00:09:23,389 --> 00:09:25,957
They're dead.

168
00:09:25,959 --> 00:09:27,992
All of them.

169
00:09:27,994 --> 00:09:31,129
Their cycle came to an end.

170
00:09:31,131 --> 00:09:34,532
And, unlike you, they won't
be brought back to life.

171
00:09:36,535 --> 00:09:38,536
You had a job:

172
00:09:38,538 --> 00:09:40,805
lead the people to be cocooned

173
00:09:40,807 --> 00:09:44,542
so that the egg could infuse
them with the life force.

174
00:09:44,544 --> 00:09:46,110
I tried.

175
00:09:46,112 --> 00:09:48,279
I did.

176
00:09:49,114 --> 00:09:52,283
I'm so sorry.

177
00:09:54,686 --> 00:09:57,288
Why were we chosen to do this?

178
00:09:57,290 --> 00:10:00,224
You and I made first contact
with the egg.

179
00:10:00,226 --> 00:10:02,727
When we touched it, we gained

180
00:10:02,729 --> 00:10:05,329
a complete understanding
of the dome's agenda:

181
00:10:05,331 --> 00:10:07,565
survive and propagate.

182
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:09,367
But I touched the egg first.

183
00:10:09,369 --> 00:10:11,903
25 years ago.

184
00:10:11,905 --> 00:10:13,971
It should have been me
inside the queen cocoon,

185
00:10:13,973 --> 00:10:15,473
not you.

186
00:10:15,475 --> 00:10:18,209
But you died
during the download.

187
00:10:18,211 --> 00:10:20,478
Three weeks ago, I came along.

188
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:22,847
From inside my cocoon,
I could see

189
00:10:22,849 --> 00:10:27,285
that this town was on the brink
of destroying itself.

190
00:10:27,287 --> 00:10:29,387
What is that stuff?

191
00:10:29,389 --> 00:10:32,890
Oxytocin. It's a mood regulator.

192
00:10:32,892 --> 00:10:36,394
It, plus the alternate reality,
was essential

193
00:10:36,396 --> 00:10:39,864
to shape these humans
into a functioning collective,

194
00:10:39,866 --> 00:10:42,400
so that we could gain
a foothold.

195
00:10:42,402 --> 00:10:44,302
Except...

196
00:10:44,304 --> 00:10:48,339
the transfer of the life force
was interrupted.

197
00:10:48,341 --> 00:10:52,009
Because Big Jim
destroyed the egg.

198
00:10:52,011 --> 00:10:53,644
Because you didn't protect it.

199
00:10:53,646 --> 00:10:56,080
Everyone who was cocooned

200
00:10:56,082 --> 00:10:57,815
has a role to play.

201
00:10:57,817 --> 00:11:00,017
We need to finish
what we started.

202
00:11:00,019 --> 00:11:01,085
Quickly.

203
00:11:01,087 --> 00:11:02,820
Well, I can't go up there.

204
00:11:02,822 --> 00:11:05,590
I'm surprised Julia hasn't come
looking for me already.

205
00:11:05,592 --> 00:11:07,625
I'll assess the townspeople

206
00:11:07,627 --> 00:11:09,560
and determine how much work
is left to do.

207
00:11:09,562 --> 00:11:10,628
You handle Julia.

208
00:11:10,630 --> 00:11:12,897
If she shows up, kill her.

209
00:11:18,237 --> 00:11:19,303
- Hey.
- Hey, Jim.

210
00:11:19,305 --> 00:11:20,538
How are you?

211
00:11:20,540 --> 00:11:21,539
Jim.
Hey, there.

212
00:11:21,541 --> 00:11:23,174
- How are you guys?
- How are you?

213
00:11:23,176 --> 00:11:24,978
Let's get this meeting started.

214
00:11:25,014 --> 00:11:26,844
Abby.

215
00:11:26,846 --> 00:11:28,779
Water?

216
00:11:28,781 --> 00:11:30,014
It's clean.

217
00:11:30,016 --> 00:11:31,349
From my well.

218
00:11:31,982 --> 00:11:33,451
It's good to see you all.

219
00:11:33,453 --> 00:11:34,819
Safe.

220
00:11:34,821 --> 00:11:37,388
Right back here
in Chester's Mill.

221
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:39,490
You think we're gonna
listen to you, Jim?

222
00:11:39,492 --> 00:11:41,492
You ran this town
into the ground.

223
00:11:41,494 --> 00:11:43,828
No, Roger, I didn't.

224
00:11:43,830 --> 00:11:47,498
I risked everything

225
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:51,035
to set you free
from those cocoons.

226
00:11:51,037 --> 00:11:53,304
Because I love this town.

227
00:11:53,306 --> 00:11:55,206
And I'd do anything for it.

228
00:11:55,208 --> 00:11:57,675
I'll get you back on your feet.

229
00:11:57,677 --> 00:11:58,910
But first things first.

230
00:11:58,912 --> 00:12:00,745
We need answers.

231
00:12:00,747 --> 00:12:02,046
For you, for all of you.

232
00:12:02,048 --> 00:12:03,748
For my son.

233
00:12:03,750 --> 00:12:06,918
The person that has
those answers is Melanie Cross.

234
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:10,755
And I won't stop
until we find that girl.

235
00:12:10,757 --> 00:12:12,823
He's starting a witch
hunt for Melanie.

236
00:12:12,825 --> 00:12:14,692
They'll kill her before
we get any answers.

237
00:12:14,694 --> 00:12:16,761
She knows what's
going on in this town

238
00:12:16,763 --> 00:12:17,963
and I'm gonna find out
what it is.

239
00:12:17,999 --> 00:12:19,197
Forget Melanie.

240
00:12:19,199 --> 00:12:21,065
You're the biggest threat
this town's ever seen.

241
00:12:21,067 --> 00:12:22,867
- Hey.
- Barbie!

242
00:12:23,735 --> 00:12:24,835
I saved everyone in there!

243
00:12:24,837 --> 00:12:25,870
Barbie!

244
00:12:25,872 --> 00:12:26,904
Enough!

245
00:12:26,906 --> 00:12:29,207
Dale!

246
00:12:38,317 --> 00:12:41,319
Who are you?

247
00:12:50,179 --> 00:12:51,968
Answer the question.

248
00:12:52,004 --> 00:12:53,837
Who are you?

249
00:12:53,839 --> 00:12:55,839
I'm Christine Price

250
00:12:55,841 --> 00:12:57,440
and this is my friend Eva.

251
00:12:57,442 --> 00:12:59,910
Excuse me, I need some air.

252
00:13:01,579 --> 00:13:04,347
And you all know each other?

253
00:13:06,617 --> 00:13:07,984
Yeah. We do.

254
00:13:07,986 --> 00:13:10,287
Eva and I were in the...

255
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:13,089
alternate reality,
as strange as it sounds.

256
00:13:13,091 --> 00:13:14,524
Sounds pretty strange.

257
00:13:14,526 --> 00:13:16,026
Everyone in the cocoons

258
00:13:16,028 --> 00:13:18,361
was from Chester's Mill.

259
00:13:18,363 --> 00:13:19,462
But you're not.

260
00:13:19,464 --> 00:13:21,898
No, no. We...

261
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:23,233
We were here on vacation.

262
00:13:23,235 --> 00:13:25,302
We went for a hike
in the woods and...

263
00:13:25,304 --> 00:13:27,282
wandered off the trail and...

264
00:13:27,318 --> 00:13:27,832
And then what?

265
00:13:27,868 --> 00:13:29,839
We stepped into
some kind of a sinkhole,

266
00:13:29,841 --> 00:13:31,875
and emerged

267
00:13:31,877 --> 00:13:33,376
from those cocoons yesterday,

268
00:13:33,378 --> 00:13:34,511
along with everybody else.

269
00:13:34,513 --> 00:13:37,147
When did you go on this hike?

270
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,049
Three weeks ago.

271
00:13:39,051 --> 00:13:40,884
That's some story.

272
00:13:40,886 --> 00:13:42,786
I'm a therapist.

273
00:13:42,788 --> 00:13:45,789
I helped this town
recover from a trauma...

274
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:46,990
in the cocoons.

275
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:49,259
It seems as if people could use

276
00:13:49,261 --> 00:13:51,328
that same kind of help now?

277
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:53,263
Shall we?

278
00:13:58,602 --> 00:14:00,070
You're staying out here.

279
00:14:00,072 --> 00:14:01,504
Or what?

280
00:14:03,107 --> 00:14:04,941
Or we tell them everything.

281
00:14:04,943 --> 00:14:06,609
Rebecca...

282
00:14:06,611 --> 00:14:07,877
Andrea...

283
00:14:07,879 --> 00:14:09,546
You shot Junior.

284
00:14:09,548 --> 00:14:11,047
How you came after me.

285
00:14:11,049 --> 00:14:12,916
After all I did for you
in those caves?

286
00:14:12,918 --> 00:14:14,918
That doesn't undo
everything else.

287
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,786
Chester's Mill's still
better off without you.

288
00:14:16,788 --> 00:14:18,888
Is it?

289
00:14:18,890 --> 00:14:20,023
Cocoons,

290
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:22,759
alternate reality...

291
00:14:22,761 --> 00:14:23,860
Yeah.

292
00:14:23,862 --> 00:14:25,428
Looks like everyone's shaken up.

293
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:27,630
Except for Christine Price.

294
00:14:37,842 --> 00:14:40,410
In the cocoons, we were
back with our families

295
00:14:40,412 --> 00:14:42,779
and now we are stuck here,
again, because of you,

296
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:45,115
because of Melanie.

297
00:14:45,117 --> 00:14:46,449
You gonna do something about it?

298
00:14:46,451 --> 00:14:48,351
Look, I-I promise you,
I'll find Melanie.

299
00:14:48,353 --> 00:14:52,188
All right? I'll get us all
the answers that we need.

300
00:14:52,190 --> 00:14:53,590
What do <i>we</i> do?

301
00:14:55,326 --> 00:14:57,060
I lost my home, too.

302
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:58,995
If you have a house,

303
00:14:58,997 --> 00:15:01,498
open your doors.

304
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,800
Let's share what we have.

305
00:15:03,802 --> 00:15:05,969
The last time I stood
in front of you,

306
00:15:05,971 --> 00:15:09,172
I urged you to find strength
in community.

307
00:15:09,174 --> 00:15:11,141
We all have something
to contribute.

308
00:15:11,143 --> 00:15:13,343
There's gotta be wildlife
out there.

309
00:15:13,345 --> 00:15:14,377
Joe.

310
00:15:14,379 --> 00:15:17,480
You can build traps.

311
00:15:17,482 --> 00:15:19,249
Or I could help find Melanie.

312
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:21,317
No, Christine's right.
We need to eat.

313
00:15:21,319 --> 00:15:22,519
I'll handle Melanie.

314
00:15:22,521 --> 00:15:24,287
Well, isn't there food
at Andrea's house?

315
00:15:24,289 --> 00:15:25,855
In the root cellar.

316
00:15:25,857 --> 00:15:27,023
Someone can take my car.

317
00:15:27,025 --> 00:15:27,991
I'll go.

318
00:15:27,993 --> 00:15:29,592
I'll go with you.

319
00:15:29,594 --> 00:15:31,795
And I'll set up an office,
here in this building.

320
00:15:31,797 --> 00:15:34,831
If anybody needs support,
come find me.

321
00:15:38,837 --> 00:15:40,470
Sam.

322
00:15:40,472 --> 00:15:42,572
There's a lot
of overwhelmed people here.

323
00:15:42,574 --> 00:15:44,140
Do you think you could
start a support group?

324
00:15:44,142 --> 00:15:45,775
Why would I do that?

325
00:15:45,777 --> 00:15:47,177
Your AA experience
in the prison.

326
00:15:47,179 --> 00:15:48,244
You could apply it here.

327
00:15:48,246 --> 00:15:50,146
People in this town
see me as a murderer,

328
00:15:50,148 --> 00:15:51,648
- not a counselor.
- Just...

329
00:15:51,650 --> 00:15:53,149
think about it.

330
00:15:53,151 --> 00:15:56,219
And... do you think
you could find your nephew?

331
00:15:56,221 --> 00:15:57,787
I didn't see him here.

332
00:16:03,094 --> 00:16:05,728
She called you "Dale."

333
00:16:05,730 --> 00:16:07,897
Julia, I said I don't
want to talk about it.

334
00:16:07,899 --> 00:16:10,733
The woman you had
a relationship with

335
00:16:10,735 --> 00:16:12,702
is suddenly here, in the flesh.

336
00:16:12,704 --> 00:16:14,604
Of course I have questions.

337
00:16:14,606 --> 00:16:16,473
Don't you?

338
00:16:16,475 --> 00:16:17,974
Yeah.

339
00:16:17,976 --> 00:16:19,042
I do.

340
00:16:19,044 --> 00:16:21,511
About things
that really happened.

341
00:16:21,513 --> 00:16:23,580
I was in a cocoon,

342
00:16:23,582 --> 00:16:24,647
my father's dead,

343
00:16:24,649 --> 00:16:25,615
you were nearly killed

344
00:16:25,617 --> 00:16:27,059
and Melanie can
answer for it all.

345
00:16:27,095 --> 00:16:29,085
We need to find her.

346
00:16:29,087 --> 00:16:31,020
So, please, can we do that?

347
00:17:04,089 --> 00:17:06,322
He's right, you're weak,
you're weak, you're pathetic.

348
00:17:06,324 --> 00:17:08,758
Just-just-just
do something right

349
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:10,293
for once in your life.

350
00:17:13,731 --> 00:17:14,964
No!

351
00:17:17,535 --> 00:17:19,269
Go away, Sam.
Leave me alone.

352
00:17:19,271 --> 00:17:20,370
Go away!

353
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:24,641
What's so bad that
you gotta end it all?

354
00:17:24,643 --> 00:17:25,842
Come on.

355
00:17:25,844 --> 00:17:27,243
Tell me.

356
00:17:28,913 --> 00:17:32,248
The life we had,
in the cocoons?

357
00:17:32,250 --> 00:17:34,184
I saw the world.
I...

358
00:17:34,186 --> 00:17:37,086
I knew what it was like
to be my own man,

359
00:17:37,088 --> 00:17:38,755
to be free from my father,

360
00:17:38,757 --> 00:17:41,991
and I can't be back
under this dome with him again.

361
00:17:43,761 --> 00:17:46,596
I'd rather be dead.

362
00:17:53,671 --> 00:17:55,672
Congratulations, kid.

363
00:17:57,508 --> 00:17:58,541
For what?

364
00:17:58,543 --> 00:18:01,511
Hitting bottom.

365
00:18:01,513 --> 00:18:04,314
You gotta get here
before you're ready to change.

366
00:18:04,316 --> 00:18:06,082
Whatever you found

367
00:18:06,084 --> 00:18:09,319
in that other life
can help you here.

368
00:18:13,157 --> 00:18:14,591
Give me the gun.

369
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,865
It works.

370
00:18:23,436 --> 00:18:25,201
There's more supplies
in Andrea's garage.

371
00:18:25,203 --> 00:18:27,403
I'll get them and set up
the traps around the property.

372
00:18:27,405 --> 00:18:28,938
Do you want to help me?

373
00:18:28,940 --> 00:18:31,174
It's been a while since we've
wandered around those woods.

374
00:18:31,176 --> 00:18:34,310
We're not here for nature,
we're here to get food.

375
00:18:34,312 --> 00:18:36,846
And then we have to take it back
and set it up for everyone.

376
00:18:36,848 --> 00:18:38,414
First you volunteer
to schlep cans,

377
00:18:38,416 --> 00:18:41,117
and now you're throwing a dinner
party for a town you hate?

378
00:18:41,119 --> 00:18:43,786
Well...
we're all in it together.

379
00:18:43,788 --> 00:18:45,755
Root cellar's out back.

380
00:18:45,757 --> 00:18:46,756
Come on, Zeta.

381
00:18:46,758 --> 00:18:48,558
Let's grab us
some cans of corn.

382
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,793
We'll meet you back at the car.

383
00:18:50,795 --> 00:18:52,595
How does he know what
sorority you joined?

384
00:18:52,597 --> 00:18:55,431
I... saw him when we were
back at the memorial.

385
00:18:55,433 --> 00:18:56,966
I must've told him.

386
00:19:06,944 --> 00:19:09,712
You're really going
to counsel people?

387
00:19:09,714 --> 00:19:12,081
Until someone else steps in.

388
00:19:12,083 --> 00:19:15,218
I've got a PhD
in biological anthropology.

389
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:17,520
I know enough to coach people
through a crisis.

390
00:19:17,522 --> 00:19:20,156
Do we really need to lie
about who we are?

391
00:19:21,292 --> 00:19:23,726
We need to keep their trust.

392
00:19:23,728 --> 00:19:25,128
We're trapped here;

393
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:27,397
the most important thing
is survival.

394
00:19:27,399 --> 00:19:30,266
When did you become
so calculating?

395
00:19:30,268 --> 00:19:32,302
Please.

396
00:19:32,304 --> 00:19:36,139
Remember when we found
that meteorite in North Dakota?

397
00:19:36,141 --> 00:19:38,408
Who negotiated our exit
with that wolf?

398
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:44,213
We've been through
so much together.

399
00:19:44,215 --> 00:19:45,214
We'll get through this.

400
00:19:45,216 --> 00:19:47,517
But first, we got work to do.

401
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:49,285
- What's that?
- Well, I'll stay here

402
00:19:49,287 --> 00:19:51,788
and try to calm people down.

403
00:19:51,790 --> 00:19:54,924
You go find the one thing
that could expose us.

404
00:19:54,926 --> 00:19:57,827
I... I don't even know
where to start.

405
00:19:57,829 --> 00:20:01,764
We have found the remains
of ancient civilizations.

406
00:20:01,766 --> 00:20:04,100
I'm sure you can handle this.

407
00:20:40,264 --> 00:20:41,731
She's not here.

408
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:52,242
That's where you were.

409
00:20:57,315 --> 00:20:59,616
And that's where I saw
Melanie put the egg...

410
00:20:59,618 --> 00:21:02,085
right before she
tried to kill me.

411
00:21:05,156 --> 00:21:06,790
But you saved her.

412
00:21:06,792 --> 00:21:08,358
Protected her.

413
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:10,627
Yeah, and then she turned on me.

414
00:21:10,629 --> 00:21:13,630
And you can't deny
what she led you into.

415
00:21:18,736 --> 00:21:20,770
Everyone in these
cocoons was connected.

416
00:21:20,772 --> 00:21:22,839
You and Eva were
together for a reason.

417
00:21:22,841 --> 00:21:24,474
Here we go.

418
00:21:24,476 --> 00:21:26,409
- Now we're back on this again.
- We are.

419
00:21:26,411 --> 00:21:28,578
Barbie, I saw the way
you looked at her.

420
00:21:28,580 --> 00:21:31,615
You were together for
what felt like a year.

421
00:21:31,617 --> 00:21:33,950
That is so much longer
than we've been together,

422
00:21:33,952 --> 00:21:36,353
so I understand if you
still have feelings.

423
00:21:36,355 --> 00:21:38,722
You were not in one
of these things, Julia.

424
00:21:38,724 --> 00:21:41,791
You can't possibly
understand any of this.

425
00:21:41,793 --> 00:21:44,494
I'm trying, but you
won't talk to me.

426
00:21:44,496 --> 00:21:47,597
You're different somehow.

427
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:51,968
Did you love her?

428
00:21:58,609 --> 00:22:00,443
I'm gonna keep looking
for Melanie.

429
00:22:03,514 --> 00:22:06,049
The tunnel branches off
about 30 paces down.

430
00:22:10,354 --> 00:22:12,522
I'll be fine.

431
00:22:40,685 --> 00:22:42,018
Git...

432
00:22:42,020 --> 00:22:43,553
Git.

433
00:24:21,819 --> 00:24:23,887
It's better than nothing.

434
00:24:23,889 --> 00:24:25,455
Not by a lot.

435
00:24:25,457 --> 00:24:26,790
Well, maybe we can find

436
00:24:26,792 --> 00:24:29,392
a stockpile of Girl Scout
cookies somewhere in here.

437
00:24:44,108 --> 00:24:45,742
NYC Punk?

438
00:24:45,744 --> 00:24:48,878
I didn't know Andrea, but she
had serious taste in music.

439
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:51,414
It was probably her kids'.

440
00:24:51,416 --> 00:24:55,485
Unless, you know,
she also played lacrosse.

441
00:24:57,021 --> 00:24:58,822
Hey, look.

442
00:25:00,124 --> 00:25:02,792
Before there was Katniss,

443
00:25:02,794 --> 00:25:04,427
there was me at summer camp.

444
00:25:04,429 --> 00:25:08,765
No TV, no boys, just singing
and swimming and sports.

445
00:25:08,767 --> 00:25:11,968
Your camp sounds a lot like
a sorority with less beer pong.

446
00:25:18,610 --> 00:25:21,511
What's wrong?

447
00:25:26,250 --> 00:25:28,451
I want it back.

448
00:25:32,122 --> 00:25:34,324
That life.

449
00:25:36,293 --> 00:25:38,895
I was a part of something,
and it felt good.

450
00:25:40,764 --> 00:25:43,433
You know...

451
00:25:43,435 --> 00:25:45,602
there's a way we can
feel good right here...

452
00:25:47,304 --> 00:25:49,138
...under this dome.

453
00:25:55,013 --> 00:25:56,246
You're an idiot.

454
00:25:56,248 --> 00:25:58,368
You know you want to dance, so come on.

455
00:25:58,377 --> 00:25:59,082
No.

456
00:25:59,084 --> 00:26:00,416
Just a little head bob,
you know?

457
00:26:03,088 --> 00:26:05,421
All right, well,
you're welcome.

458
00:26:05,423 --> 00:26:06,789
Let's keep hunting for grub.

459
00:26:06,791 --> 00:26:08,258
The town's counting on us.

460
00:26:11,562 --> 00:26:13,429
"Support group next door."

461
00:26:18,502 --> 00:26:20,737
You're all here
to see Christine?

462
00:26:21,839 --> 00:26:23,840
She offered to help;
we need it.

463
00:26:23,842 --> 00:26:25,875
Christine was my counselor
while I was in prison.

464
00:26:25,877 --> 00:26:28,278
I learned a lot from her.

465
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:32,549
This morning, she asked me if
I would lead a support group.

466
00:26:32,551 --> 00:26:34,450
You?

467
00:26:34,452 --> 00:26:36,452
Yeah.

468
00:26:37,688 --> 00:26:39,956
I'm not staying.

469
00:26:39,958 --> 00:26:42,659
I can't just tell a bunch of
strangers all my problems.

470
00:26:42,661 --> 00:26:44,694
Junior, I don't think
you should be alone right now.

471
00:26:44,696 --> 00:26:45,962
You have my gun.

472
00:26:45,964 --> 00:26:47,830
You can't babysit me forever.

473
00:26:53,871 --> 00:26:56,139
I was giving her a bath.

474
00:26:57,942 --> 00:27:00,777
And we were singing a song
when it all ended.

475
00:27:00,779 --> 00:27:03,947
: And I can't
lose her again.

476
00:27:05,416 --> 00:27:09,319
Can you survive one hour
without your child?

477
00:27:12,156 --> 00:27:14,357
Abby?

478
00:27:16,794 --> 00:27:18,761
That's where you start.

479
00:27:18,763 --> 00:27:21,464
I'll be here any hour you need.

480
00:27:21,466 --> 00:27:23,333
For all of you.

481
00:27:29,974 --> 00:27:31,174
Hey, Junior.

482
00:27:35,746 --> 00:27:39,349
Excuse me, there's, people
in there, waiting for you.

483
00:27:39,351 --> 00:27:41,618
Shoot.

484
00:27:41,620 --> 00:27:44,253
I was out looking for food.

485
00:27:44,255 --> 00:27:46,556
It's good to see
you again, James.

486
00:27:46,558 --> 00:27:49,292
We never really met.

487
00:27:50,794 --> 00:27:52,862
How you doing?

488
00:27:52,864 --> 00:27:54,998
I'm okay.

489
00:27:56,233 --> 00:27:59,035
Now, how about the truth?

490
00:28:00,904 --> 00:28:03,072
The truth?

491
00:28:04,942 --> 00:28:06,876
I don't know how
I'm gonna survive here.

492
00:28:06,878 --> 00:28:09,212
In that other world,
I killed my father,

493
00:28:09,214 --> 00:28:12,215
I was ready
to burn down his house.

494
00:28:12,217 --> 00:28:14,250
That was the life
that I wanted...

495
00:28:14,252 --> 00:28:15,985
to be free from him.

496
00:28:15,987 --> 00:28:18,087
But... I'm here.

497
00:28:19,156 --> 00:28:21,391
You were about to
make a breakthrough.

498
00:28:24,995 --> 00:28:27,263
If you really want
to be who you were...

499
00:28:28,399 --> 00:28:30,733
...finish what you started.

500
00:28:30,735 --> 00:28:32,602
Drop the match.

501
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:37,040
We are what we do.

502
00:28:51,789 --> 00:28:53,990
We are what we do.

503
00:29:21,752 --> 00:29:24,101
Julia...!

504
00:29:35,042 --> 00:29:37,746
Everything started here.

505
00:29:54,062 --> 00:29:55,829
Are you okay?

506
00:29:55,831 --> 00:29:57,264
What happened?

507
00:29:57,266 --> 00:29:58,732
I found Ben's body.

508
00:29:58,734 --> 00:30:03,603
His neck was bruised
just like yours.

509
00:30:03,605 --> 00:30:06,721
He said he saw Melanie
in the alternate reality.

510
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:11,220
He didn't die from
an asthma attack.

511
00:30:11,256 --> 00:30:13,647
He died because she
killed him here.

512
00:30:15,750 --> 00:30:18,552
I'm sorry I left you alone.

513
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:24,257
I think all this was way more
real than I wanted to admit.

514
00:30:29,163 --> 00:30:31,364
Including Eva.

515
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:34,768
Tell me.

516
00:30:36,270 --> 00:30:38,998
I mourned you, Julia.

517
00:30:42,276 --> 00:30:44,110
Time passed.

518
00:30:48,416 --> 00:30:50,917
And I fell in love with her.

519
00:30:53,135 --> 00:30:55,889
And that, with her...

520
00:30:57,725 --> 00:30:59,926
...that feels like yesterday.

521
00:31:19,247 --> 00:31:21,181
Andrea.

522
00:31:40,736 --> 00:31:42,235
Stop.

523
00:31:45,741 --> 00:31:47,107
Hey, Davy Crockett.

524
00:31:47,109 --> 00:31:48,842
Why'd you shut the party down?

525
00:31:48,844 --> 00:31:50,243
"Party"?

526
00:31:50,245 --> 00:31:51,311
This is a crime scene.

527
00:31:51,313 --> 00:31:53,046
What the hell
did you do with Andrea?

528
00:31:53,048 --> 00:31:54,714
She was like that
when we got here.

529
00:31:54,716 --> 00:31:56,388
We covered her and moved her.

530
00:31:56,424 --> 00:31:57,517
You put her outside?

531
00:31:57,519 --> 00:31:59,019
Like trash?

532
00:31:59,021 --> 00:32:01,388
Ever smelled a dead body?

533
00:32:01,390 --> 00:32:03,657
I've known her my whole life.

534
00:32:03,659 --> 00:32:06,326
Even if you guys didn't,
she was a human being.

535
00:32:06,328 --> 00:32:08,728
Joe, she would want us to eat.

536
00:32:08,730 --> 00:32:10,330
What's the big deal
about us listening to music

537
00:32:10,332 --> 00:32:12,399
while we search for food?

538
00:32:12,401 --> 00:32:15,201
You're right.

539
00:32:26,914 --> 00:32:31,384
All right, let's see what old
Thelma and Louise are up to.

540
00:32:33,854 --> 00:32:36,156
And we're rolling.

541
00:32:36,158 --> 00:32:39,359
According to the dark flight
calculations of the meteoroid

542
00:32:39,361 --> 00:32:41,294
and magnetometer readings,

543
00:32:41,296 --> 00:32:43,897
we believe we have
located the target

544
00:32:43,899 --> 00:32:45,332
here in Chester's Mill.

545
00:32:45,334 --> 00:32:47,867
Therapist, my ass.

546
00:32:51,973 --> 00:32:54,341
Is it intact?

547
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:01,715
It's perfect!

548
00:33:01,717 --> 00:33:04,618
There's a faint
dusting of quartz.

549
00:33:04,620 --> 00:33:06,886
Possibly amethyst?

550
00:33:08,624 --> 00:33:11,858
There appears
to be some kind of...

551
00:33:11,860 --> 00:33:14,194
energy reserve.

552
00:33:14,196 --> 00:33:16,062
Christine, I think
you should put it down.

553
00:33:17,399 --> 00:33:19,265
Drop it! Drop it!

554
00:33:19,267 --> 00:33:20,300
Drop it, Christine!

555
00:33:22,671 --> 00:33:25,238
What the...?

556
00:33:34,116 --> 00:33:36,249
Junior!

557
00:33:36,251 --> 00:33:39,219
What the hell have you done?

558
00:33:39,221 --> 00:33:41,955
I'm just doing what I have
to do in order to move on.

559
00:33:41,957 --> 00:33:43,556
What?!

560
00:33:43,558 --> 00:33:44,758
Christine was right.

561
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:47,360
I need to finish
what I started.

562
00:33:47,362 --> 00:33:48,895
Christine?
Let me tell you something.

563
00:33:48,897 --> 00:33:50,557
She's not who you think she is.

564
00:33:50,593 --> 00:33:52,520
Those cocoons?
I think she's responsible.

565
00:33:52,556 --> 00:33:53,700
I should thank her.

566
00:33:53,702 --> 00:33:56,336
I've never been happier.

567
00:33:56,338 --> 00:33:59,005
This makes you happy?

568
00:33:59,007 --> 00:34:01,675
I don't feel it.

569
00:34:01,677 --> 00:34:04,044
It's gone.

570
00:34:04,046 --> 00:34:05,278
What's gone?

571
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:07,947
You.

572
00:34:07,949 --> 00:34:10,250
You don't exist.

573
00:34:10,252 --> 00:34:13,787
You're not my father anymore.

574
00:34:30,138 --> 00:34:32,172
It's okay! It's okay.

575
00:34:32,174 --> 00:34:33,840
I'm not like them.

576
00:34:33,842 --> 00:34:36,676
I'm like you... trapped.

577
00:34:37,678 --> 00:34:38,945
Go find your friends.

578
00:34:47,121 --> 00:34:50,390
Nice shot.

579
00:34:50,392 --> 00:34:52,225
Why'd you kill it?

580
00:34:52,227 --> 00:34:54,694
It's what the town needs, Joe.

581
00:35:00,267 --> 00:35:02,302
Your leg okay?

582
00:35:02,304 --> 00:35:04,504
I'm good.

583
00:35:23,758 --> 00:35:26,706
Looks like it's
just the two of us.

584
00:35:36,220 --> 00:35:37,321
Julia!

585
00:35:46,398 --> 00:35:48,365
Melanie... stop.

586
00:35:48,367 --> 00:35:50,519
I'm sorry, Julia.
This needs to happen.

587
00:35:52,070 --> 00:35:54,404
Get off!

588
00:35:56,174 --> 00:35:57,507
Melanie...

589
00:36:00,579 --> 00:36:02,551
I should've just cocooned you,
like the others!

590
00:36:02,587 --> 00:36:05,235
Things would've been
so much better.

591
00:36:21,265 --> 00:36:22,899
Are you okay?

592
00:36:33,544 --> 00:36:35,045
What happened?

593
00:36:35,047 --> 00:36:38,749
I was out looking for food
and I saw this girl.

594
00:36:38,751 --> 00:36:41,985
She, she was strangling Julia.

595
00:36:41,987 --> 00:36:44,454
My God, what've I done?!

596
00:36:45,590 --> 00:36:47,290
You saved my life.

597
00:37:15,653 --> 00:37:18,255
Guess this is as good
a place as any.

598
00:37:18,257 --> 00:37:19,823
The place where he died.

599
00:37:20,825 --> 00:37:23,860
And where Melanie
came back to life.

600
00:37:28,833 --> 00:37:32,302
Now we'll never know
why she did that to us.

601
00:37:37,608 --> 00:37:40,377
I just need a little time alone.

602
00:37:40,379 --> 00:37:43,280
Of course.

603
00:37:49,887 --> 00:37:52,355
I love you, Julia.

604
00:37:52,357 --> 00:37:54,591
We're gonna get
through this, okay?

605
00:37:56,127 --> 00:37:58,128
I love you, too.

606
00:37:58,130 --> 00:38:01,131
I'll be back in an hour.

607
00:38:02,233 --> 00:38:03,867
I'll see you back at the motel.

608
00:38:03,869 --> 00:38:05,335
Yeah.

609
00:38:15,213 --> 00:38:18,882
Overkill for a fishing trip.

610
00:38:18,884 --> 00:38:20,951
I'm getting out of here.

611
00:38:20,953 --> 00:38:24,755
You're leaving town?

612
00:38:24,757 --> 00:38:26,857
Do you know what happens
inside a cocoon?

613
00:38:26,859 --> 00:38:29,626
That fuzzy little caterpillar
liquefies.

614
00:38:29,628 --> 00:38:32,229
And when it comes out,

615
00:38:32,231 --> 00:38:33,830
it's something else.

616
00:38:33,832 --> 00:38:36,733
Those people, they're,

617
00:38:36,735 --> 00:38:38,368
they're not the same.

618
00:38:38,370 --> 00:38:40,036
Well, of course they're not.

619
00:38:40,038 --> 00:38:42,572
Think about what
they've been through.

620
00:38:42,574 --> 00:38:44,541
No, I mean they're
not the same.

621
00:38:44,543 --> 00:38:45,942
They've changed.

622
00:38:45,944 --> 00:38:47,944
Junior, he-he burned
down the house,

623
00:38:47,946 --> 00:38:51,281
and whistled while it blazed,
all dead behind the eyes.

624
00:38:51,283 --> 00:38:53,383
He finally stood up to you.

625
00:38:53,385 --> 00:38:55,252
I know my son.

626
00:38:55,254 --> 00:38:57,320
That's not him.

627
00:38:57,322 --> 00:39:00,590
You think your precious
little Barbie's the same?

628
00:39:00,592 --> 00:39:02,692
- No way.
- Barbie and I are gonna be

629
00:39:02,694 --> 00:39:05,629
just fine.

630
00:39:05,631 --> 00:39:07,063
But you?

631
00:39:07,065 --> 00:39:10,367
You're run out of town.

632
00:39:10,369 --> 00:39:11,968
You do whatever you need to

633
00:39:11,970 --> 00:39:14,638
to rationalize that.

634
00:39:14,640 --> 00:39:17,908
Listen.

635
00:39:17,910 --> 00:39:20,677
I'm right about them.

636
00:39:20,679 --> 00:39:23,246
Just like I was right
about everything else.

637
00:39:31,856 --> 00:39:34,391
Get out of here.

638
00:39:34,393 --> 00:39:36,960
Get out of my boat!

639
00:39:39,598 --> 00:39:41,965
Go home.

640
00:39:57,516 --> 00:40:00,250
You ever hear
of the designated survivor?

641
00:40:00,252 --> 00:40:02,752
He goes off on
his own when the...

642
00:40:02,754 --> 00:40:04,321
president and all the bigwigs

643
00:40:04,323 --> 00:40:07,157
are doing
the State of the Union.

644
00:40:09,927 --> 00:40:13,396
Well, bud, that's you and me.

645
00:40:13,398 --> 00:40:15,866
We're gonna be out there
on Bird Island.

646
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:44,794
<i>James was the closest...</i>

647
00:40:44,796 --> 00:40:47,030
<i>a seed, ready to sprout...</i>

648
00:40:47,032 --> 00:40:48,899
<i>once he shed his fear.</i>

649
00:40:48,901 --> 00:40:52,569
<i>With the right amount of
nurturing, Sam could be next.</i>

650
00:40:52,571 --> 00:40:55,839
<i>They came when I signaled,
without knowing why.</i>

651
00:40:55,841 --> 00:40:59,142
<i>The life force has taken root.</i>

652
00:40:59,144 --> 00:41:03,813
<i>Some are compelled
to serve their duties.</i>

653
00:41:03,815 --> 00:41:07,450
<i>Some will require cultivation.</i>

654
00:41:07,452 --> 00:41:11,688
<i>Others must be pruned away.</i>

655
00:41:13,157 --> 00:41:16,459
<i>Weeds are stronger
than they seem,</i>

656
00:41:16,461 --> 00:41:19,596
<i>a threat to what must blossom.</i>

657
00:41:20,731 --> 00:41:23,566
<i>But, with careful tending,</i>

658
00:41:23,568 --> 00:41:28,038
<i>this kinship will grow
into what we need it to be.</i>
